§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ What of the conditional densities of a multivariate normal
    density. ⦉
⦉

§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ¶ ⦊
    ‖ Let $f: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$ be a normal density with mean $μ ∈
      𝗥^d$ and covariance $Σ ∈ 𝗦^d$.
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ μ = \bmat{μ_x ᜶ μ_y} \quad \text{ and } \quad ⦉

        ‖ Σ = \bmat{ ⦉

        ‖ Σ_{xx} & Σ_{xy} ᜶ ⦉

        ‖ Σ_{yx} & Σ_{yy} ⦉

        ‖ } ⦉
      ⦉⦉
  ⦉

  ¶ ⦊
    ‖ The conditional density $f_{x |y}(ξ, γ)$ is
      $\normal{\bar{μ}(γ)}{\bar{Σ}}$ where
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ \bar{μ}(γ) = μ_1 + Σ_{xy}Σ_{yy}^{-1}(γ - μ_y) \text{
          and } \bar{Σ} = Σ_{xx} - Σ_{xy}Σ_{yy}^{-1}Σ_{yx}. ⦉
      ⦉⦉
  ⦉
</statement>
